# Prometheus LLM Configuration Examples

The new per-provider helper layout (see
`prometheus/config/providers/`) means most providers only need a name
and a model id; the helper supplies the base URL, env-var fallback,
and any provider-specific quirks (like the OpenRouter → DeepSeek
tool_choice quirk).

## TokenRouter (default)

```yaml
providers:
  tokenrouter:
    api_keys:
      - env: TOKENROUTER_API_KEY
    models:
      MiniMax-M3:
        tier: hard
        max_tokens: 256000
        context_window: 524288
        supports_thinking: true

routing:
  simple:  [tokenrouter/MiniMax-M3]
  medium:  [tokenrouter/MiniMax-M3]
  hard:    [tokenrouter/MiniMax-M3]

defaults:
  tier: hard
```

## OpenRouter (with openrouter/auto router)

`openrouter/auto` is automatically flagged with
`drop_tool_choice_with_thinking=True` and `force_store_false=True`
because the upstream is unknown at config time and may be DeepSeek.

```yaml
providers:
  openrouter:
    api_keys:
      - env: OPENROUTER_API_KEY
    models:
      openrouter/auto:
        tier: hard
        max_tokens: 65536
      anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6:
        tier: standard

routing:
  hard:     [openrouter/openrouter/auto]
  standard: [openrouter/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6]
```

## DeepSeek

```yaml
providers:
  deepseek:
    api_keys:
      - env: DEEPSEEK_API_KEY
    models:
      deepseek-chat:
        tier: medium
      deepseek-reasoner:
        tier: hard
        supports_thinking: true
```

## Anthropic (Messages API)

```yaml
providers:
  anthropic:
    api_keys:
      - env: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
    models:
      claude-sonnet-4-6:
        tier: standard
```

## Custom endpoint (any OpenAI- or Anthropic-compatible vendor)

Use `custom` (or set `type: custom` on a named provider) when the
provider is not in the registry. You pick the protocol explicitly.

```yaml
providers:
  # OpenAI-compatible internal proxy
  internal-gateway:
    type: custom
    base_url: https://llm.internal/v1
    protocol: openai            # or: anthropic
    api_keys:
      - env: MY_GATEWAY_KEY
    extra_headers:
      X-Org: acme
    models:
      llama-3.1-70b-internal:
        tier: hard

  # Or, equivalently, use the generic "custom" provider
  custom:
    base_url: https://self-hosted-litellm/v1
    protocol: openai
    api_keys:
      - env: LITELLM_KEY
    models:
      mixtral-8x7b:
        tier: medium
```

## Opting out of a named helper

If a provider name collides with a helper (e.g. you want
`openrouter` with a non-default base URL and none of its default
quirks), set `type: custom`:

```yaml
providers:
  openrouter:
    type: custom
    base_url: https://my-fork.example/v1
    protocol: openai
    models:
      openrouter/auto:
        tier: hard
```

## Adding a new provider

1. Drop a `myprovider.py` next to `tokenrouter.py`.
2. Implement `build_helper()` returning a `ProviderHelper`.
3. Register it in `prometheus/config/providers/__init__.py`.

The loader picks it up automatically; no other wiring required.
